<LayerPage
  eyebrow="Ring · how it is controlled"
  layerTag="L4 · Governance & GRC"
  title="Governance is what keeps it accountable over time."
  lede="Sovereign architecture keeps your data in; governance is what proves the system stays controlled, owned and answerable as it lives and changes. The AI management system, the risk register, the named owners and the review cadence that turn a deployment into something a regulator will accept."
  seoTitle={seoTitle}
  seoDescription={seoDescription}
  points={points}
  standards={standards}
>
  <!-- Why governance is the differentiator -->
  <section class="bg-white dark:bg-black border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800">
    <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 py-20">
      <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-olive-600 dark:text-olive-400 mb-4">Why this ring is the differentiator</p>
      <h2 class="text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-6">
        The hyperscalers give you a container. We govern the behaviour.
      </h2>
      <div class="space-y-5 text-lg text-zinc-700 dark:text-zinc-300 leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          A sovereign container — data in the UK, encrypted, on hardware you control — is
          necessary, but it is not enough for generative AI. The model is a new kind of asset:
          it acts, it decides, and it can be wrong in ways a database never could. Governance
          is the layer that makes those decisions <strong>accountable</strong>.
        </p>
        <p>
          This is where we and our security layer pull ahead of "sovereign" alternatives that
          stop at residency. We do not just keep the data in; we govern the AI to ISO 42001,
          classify its risk, name its owners and produce the evidence — so the system is not
          only <em>private</em>, it is <em>defensible</em>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- What the AIMS contains -->
  <section class="bg-zinc-50 dark:bg-zinc-950 border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 py-20">
      <p class="text-xs font-mono uppercase tracking-widest text-olive-600 dark:text-olive-400 mb-4">Inside the management system</p>
      <h2 class="text-2xl md:text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-8">
        Four things every regulated AI deployment needs.
      </h2>
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
        <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800">
          <div class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-1">An AI policy</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">What the organisation will and will not do with AI, signed off and reviewed.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800">
          <div class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-1">A system register</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">Every model and use case logged, risk-classified and owned by a named person.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800">
          <div class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-1">Impact assessments</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">DPIA and AI risk assessment delivered with the deployment, not after an incident.</div>
        </div>
        <div class="p-6 rounded-xl bg-white dark:bg-zinc-900 border border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800">
          <div class="font-semibold text-zinc-900 dark:text-white mb-1">A review cadence</div>
          <div class="text-sm text-zinc-500 dark:text-zinc-400">Scheduled reviews so the controls stay true as the model and the rules change.</div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- The rings around it -->
  <section class="bg-white dark:bg-black border-b border-zinc-200 dark:border-zinc-800">
    <div class="max-w-5xl mx-auto px-6 lg:px-8 py-20">
